fInterp3D(double[][][], double[], double[]) - Static method in class optimisme.MMCal
This static method fInterp3D realizes the cubic 3D interpolation in the new resolution
fInterp3DTest() - Method in class optimisme.test.PSFPreparatorTest
 
freqfilt3D(double[][][], int, int, int) - Static method in class optimisme.MMCal
This static method freqfilt3D returns the complex frequency output 3D data the output array is of size slices by rows by 2*columns, physical layout of the output data is as follows: a[k3][k2][2*k1] = Re[k3][k2][k1], a[k3][k2][2*k1+1] = Im[k3][k2][k1], 0<=k3<slices, 0<=k2<columns, 0<=k1<rows,
